            <bioghist>
                <p>The 315th Infantry Association was founded in 1920 by veterans of the 315th
                    Infantry Regiment who served in France during World War I. The 315th, which was
                    part of the 79th Division during World War I, consisted mostly of men from the
                    Philadelphia area and was known as "Philadelphia's own."</p>
            </bioghist>

            <scopecontent>
                <p>This is a collection of materials related to the 315th Infantry Association.
                    Materials include: minutes, 1920-1983; financial records; charter;
                    correspondence; member and burial lists; association newsletters and other
                    periodicals; and photos, clippings, pamphlets, and invitations. </p>
            </scopecontent>

